name: Air Fryer Corned Beef Hash
author: Soup Loving Nicole
summary: Looking for something to do with leftover corned beef? This crispy corned beef hash is made from start to finish in the air fryer.
ingredients: ½ cup chopped green bell pepper
salt and ground black pepper to taste
directions: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Combine potatoes, bell pepper, and onion in a large bowl
Add vegetable oil, paprika, salt, and pepper
Stir until potatoes are evenly coated
Transfer mixture to the basket of the air fryer
Shake and cook 5 for minutes more
Stir in the corned beef and cook for 5 minutes
Make 2 small wells in the mixture
Cook until eggs are set and cooked to desired doneness, about 3 minutes
